{"title_page": "W3Schools", "text_new": "{{short description|Web developer information website}}\n{{Infobox website\n| name             = W3Schools\n| logo             = W3Schools logo.png\n| screenshot       = \n| caption          = \n| url              = {{url|https://www.w3schools.com}}\n| commercial       = Yes\n| language         = Multiple languages\n| type             = Web development portal\n| registration     = Required for [[Internet forum|forum]]\n| owner            = Refsnes Data\n| author           = Refsnes Data\n| alexa            = {{Increase}} 180 <small>({{as of|2020|3|24|alt=March 2020}})</small><ref name=\"alexa\">{{cite web|url= https://www.alexa.com/siteinfo/w3schools.com#trafficstatsm |title= W3schools.com Site Info | publisher= [[Alexa Internet]] |accessdate= 2019-10-06}}</ref>\n| launch_date      = 1998\n| current_status   = Active\n}}\n\n'''W3Schools''' is an educational website for learning web technologies online.<ref name=\"alexa\"/> Content includes tutorials and references relating to [[HTML]], [[CSS]], [[JavaScript]], [[JSON]], [[PHP]], [[Python (programming language)|Python]], [[AngularJS]], [[React (web framework)|React.js]], [[SQL]], [[Bootstrap (front-end framework)|Bootstrap]], [[Sass (stylesheet language)|Sass]], [[Node.js]],  [[jQuery]], [[XQuery]], [[Ajax (programming)|AJAX]], [[XML]], [[Raspberry Pi]], [[C++]], [[C_Sharp_(programming_language)|C#]] and [[Java (programming language)|Java]].\n\nCreated in 1998, its name is derived from the [[World Wide Web]], but is not affiliated with the W3C ([[World Wide Web Consortium]]).<ref name=\":0\">{{cite web|url=https://www.w3schools.com/about/ |title=About W3Schools |website=W3schools.com |date= |accessdate=2016-08-09}}</ref> It is run by Refsnes Data in Norway.<ref>{{cit web|first1=Hege|first2=St\u00e5le|first3=Jan Egil|last1=Refsnes|last2=Refsnes|last3=Refsnes|title=About Refsnes Data|url=http://www.w3schools.com/about/about_refsnes.asp|archivedate=2008-04-21|archiveurl=https://w