ano Rodr\u00edguez]]\n|43\n|{{bk|NED}}\n|[[EuroBasket 1967|1967 EuroBasket 1st Round]]\n|1967.10.05\n|Helsinki (FIN)\n|-\n|[[Pau Gasol]]\n|40\n|{{bk|FRA}}\n|[[EuroBasket 2015|2015 EuroBasket Semifinal]]\n|2015.09.17\n|Lille (FRA)\n|-\n|[[Wayne Brabender]]\n|40\n|{{bk|FRA}}\n|[[FIBA World Olympic Qualifying Tournament|1980 Olympics qualification]]\n|1980.05.14\n|Geneva (SUI)\n|-\n|[[Pau Gasol]]\n|37\n|{{bk|CHN}}\n|[[Basketball at the 2004 Summer Olympics|2004 Olympics Classification Round]]\n|2004.08.28\n|Athens (GRE)\n|-\n|[[Wayne Brabender]]\n|37\n|{{Bk|PHI}}\n|[[1974 FIBA World Championship|1974 World Cup 1st Round]]\n|1974.07.05\n|Ponce (PUR)\n|-\n|[[Emiliano Rodr\u00edguez]]\n|37\n|{{Bk|GDR}}\n|[[EuroBasket 1963|1963 EuroBasket 1st Round]]\n|1963.10.09\n|Wroclaw (POL)\n|-\n|[[Juan Carlos Navarro (basketball)|Juan Carlos Navarro]]\n|36\n|{{bk|CRO}}\n|[[EuroBasket 2005|2005 EuroBasket Quarterfinal]]\n|2005.09.23\n|Novi Sad (SRB)\n|-\n|[[Pau Gasol]]\n|36\n|{{bk|LTU}}\n|[[EuroBasket 2003|2003 EuroBasket Final]]\n|2003.09.14\n|S\u00f6dert\u00e4lje (SWE)\n|-\n|[[Juan Antonio San Epifanio|Epi]]\n|36\n|{{Bk|West Germany}}\n|[[EuroBasket 1985|1985 EuroBasket Quarterfinal]]\n|1985.06.11\n|Sttutgart (GER)\n|}\n\n===Top medallists===\n:''For a full list of all the 95 medallists with the senior team since 1935, see [[Medal winners in Spain men's national basketball team]]''\nMost medals won with the senior national team in ([[Basketball at the Summer Olympics|Olympic Games]], [[FIBA World Cup|World Cups]] and [[EuroBasket]]s):\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!style=\"width:160px;\"| Player\n! Medals\n! Details\n|-\n| [[Pau Gasol]]\n| 11\n| {{collapse top}}\n* <small>{{Eur3}} [[EuroBasket 2001|2001 EuroBasket]]</small>\n* <small>{{Eur2}} [[EuroBasket 2003|2003 EuroBasket]]</small>\n* <small>{{World1}} [[2006 FIBA World Championship|2006 FIBA World Cup]]</small>\n* <small>{{Eur2}} [[EuroBasket 2007|2007 EuroBasket]]</small>\n* <small>{{OG2}} [[Basketball at the 2008 Summer Olympics