ics]]<br />4th [[1985 EuroBasket]]<br />5th [[1986 FIBA World Championship|1986 World Cup]]<br />4th [[1987 EuroBasket]]<br />8th [[Basketball at the 1988 Summer Olympics|1988 Summer Olympics]]<br />5th [[1989 Eurobasket]]<br />10th [[1990 FIBA World Championship|1990 World Cup]]<br />{{Eur3}} [[EuroBasket 1991|1991 EuroBasket]]<br />9th [[Basketball at the 1992 Summer Olympics|1992 Summer Olympics]]\n|-\n|1993\u20132000\n|{{flagicon|ESP}} [[Lolo Sainz]]\n|5th [[EuroBasket 1993|1993 EuroBasket]]<br/>10th [[1994 FIBA World Championship|1994 World Cup]]<br/>6th [[EuroBasket 1995|1995 EuroBasket]]<br/>5th [[EuroBasket 1997|1997 EuroBasket]]<br/>5th [[1998 FIBA World Cup|1998 World Cup]]<br/>{{Eur2}} [[EuroBasket 1999|1999 EuroBasket]]<br/>9th [[Basketball at the 2000 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's tournament|2000 Summer Olympics]]\n|-\n|2001\u20132002\n|{{flagicon|ESP}} [[Javier Imbroda]]\n|{{Eur3}} [[EuroBasket 2001|2001 EuroBasket]]<br/>5th [[2002 FIBA World Championship|2002 World Cup]]\n|-\n|2003\n|{{flagicon|ESP}} [[Moncho L\u00f3pez]]\n|{{Eur2}} [[EuroBasket 2003|2003 EuroBasket]]\n|-\n|2004\u20132005\n|{{flagicon|ESP}} [[Mario Pesquera]]\n|7th [[Basketball at the 2004 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's tournament|2004 Summer Olympics]]<br/>4th [[EuroBasket 2005|2005 EuroBasket]]\n|-\n|2006\u20132007\n|{{flagicon|ESP}} [[Pepu Hern\u00e1ndez]]\n|{{World1}} [[2006 FIBA World Championship|2006 World Cup]]<br/>{{Eur2}} [[EuroBasket 2007|2007 EuroBasket]]\n|-\n|2008\n|{{flagicon|ESP}} [[A\u00edto Garc\u00eda Reneses]]\n|{{OG2}} [[Basketball at the 2008 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's tournament|2008 Summer Olympics]]\n|-\n|2009\u20132012\n|{{flagicon|ITA}} [[Sergio Scariolo]]\n|{{Eur1}} [[EuroBasket 2009|2009 EuroBasket]]<br />6th [[2010 FIBA World Championship|2010 World Cup]]<br/>{{Eur1}} [[EuroBasket 2011|2011 EuroBasket]]<br/>{{OG2}} [[Basketball at the 2012 Summer Olympics|2012 Summer Olympics]]\n|-\n|2013\u20132014\n|{{flagicon|ESP}} [[Juan Antonio Orenga]]\n|{{Eur3}} [[EuroBasket 2013|2013 EuroBasket]]<br/>5th [[2014 FIBA World Championship|2014 World Cup]]\n|-\n|2015\u2013\n|{{flagicon|ITA}} [[Sergio Scariolo]]\n|{{Eur1}} [[EuroBasket 2015|2015 EuroBasket]]<br/>{{OG3}} [[Basketball at the 2016 Summer Olympics|2016 Summer Olympics]]<br/>{{Eur3}} [[EuroBasket 2017|2017 EuroBasket]]<br/>{{World1}} [[2019 FIBA Basketball World Cup|2019 World Cup]]\n|}\n*Most games as head coach: [[Antonio D\u00edaz-Miguel]]: 423 games, over 27 years.\n*Most medals won with the national team: (7): [[Sergio Scariolo]]\n\n==Progression in the [[FIBA World Ranking]]==\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! Date !! Change !! {{Tooltip|Pos.|Position}} !! Points !! {{Tooltip|Dis.|Distance to 1st}}\n|-\n| 11 Oct 2017 || align=center|{{steady}} || 2nd || 693.2 || \u2013126.4\n|-\n| 28 Nov 2017 || align=center|{{steady}} || 2nd || 693.8 || \u2013142.4\n|-\n| 28 Feb 2018 || align=center|{{steady}} || 2nd || 704.7 || \u201330.3\n|-\n| 3 Jul 2018 || align=center|{{steady}} || 2nd || 706.7 || \u201341.4\n|-\n| 18 Sep 2018 || align=center|{{steady}} || 2nd || 704.2 || \u201362.9\n|-\n| 4 Dec 2018 || align=center|{{steady}} || 2nd || 702.6 || \u201380.4\n|-\n| 26 Feb 2019 || align=center|{{steady}} || 2nd || 703.4 || \u201390.3\n|-\n| 19 Sep 2019 || align=center|{{steady}} || 2nd || 731.5 || \u201354.9\n|-\n| 3 Mar 2020 || align=center|{{steady}} || 2nd || 722.9 || \u201358.7\n|-\n|}\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Sports|Spain}}\n*[[Spanish Basketball Federation]]\n*[[Spain women's national basketball team]]\n*[[Spain national youth basketball teams]]\n*[[Sport in Spain]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Spain national basketball team}}\n*[http://www.seleccionbaloncesto.es/inicio.aspx Official website] {{in lang|es}}\n*[http://www.feb.es/ Federation website] {{in lang|es}}\n*[http://www.fiba.basketball/federation/Spain Spain] at FIBA site\n*[http://www.eurobasket.com/Spain/basketball-National-Team.asp