iva Films]]\n|-\n| ''[[Won't Last A Day Without You]]''\n|George Apostol/DJ Heidee\n|\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[It Takes a Man and a Woman]]''\n|Laida Magtalas\n|[[GMMSF Box-Office Entertainment Award for Box-Office Queen]]\n[[2014 FAMAS Awards]]- nominated for Best Actress\n\n2013 Highest Grossing Non-MMFF Filipino Film\n\n2014 ENPRESS Golden Screen Awards- Best Performance by an Actress in a Lead Role (Comedy/Musical)<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.philstar.com:8080/movies/2014/10/05/1376783/joel-torre-vilma-santos-lead-winners-11th-golden-screen-awards |title=Archived copy |accessdate=April 5, 2017 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170406025058/http://www.philstar.com:8080/movies/2014/10/05/1376783/joel-torre-vilma-santos-lead-winners-11th-golden-screen-awards |archivedate=April 6, 2017 }}</ref>\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[Maybe This Time (2014 film)|Maybe This Time]]''\n|Stephanie Asuncion\n|\n|-\n| 2015\n| ''[[The Breakup Playlist]]''\n|Trixie David\n| 2016 PMPC Star Awards for Movies- nominated for Movie Actress of the Year\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[Finally Found Someone]]''\n|Aprilyn Esguerra\n| Comeback Movie with [[John Lloyd Cruz]]\n|-\n| 2018\n| ''[[Miss Granny (2018 film)|Miss Granny]]''\n|Feliza \"Fely\" Malaba\u00f1o / Audrey de Leon\n| Remake of the 2015 South Korean movie [[Miss Granny|of the same title]]\n[[Star Awards 2019|2019 Star Awards]] - Best Actress winner\n\n[[2019 FAMAS Awards]] - Best Actress Nominee\n\n2019 EDDYs - Best Actress Nominee\n|[[Viva Films]] and N\u00b2\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2019\n|''[[This 15 Me World Tour|Sarah Geronimo: This 15 Me]]''\n|Herself\n|First Asian artist to have an [[Netflix original|Original]] [[concert film]] on Netflix\n|[[Netflix]]\n|-\n|''[[Unforgettable (2019 film)|Unforgettable]]''\n|Jasmine Lagman\n|\n|[[Viva Films]] and The Idea First Company\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Network\n|-\n| 1992\u20131994\n| ''[[Penpen De Sarapen]]''\n| Herself/Performer\n|