aceutical Trust]]\n*[[Ditt Apotek]]\n*[[Northern Norway Pharmaceutical Trust]]\n*[[Southern and Eastern Norway Pharmaceutical Trust]]\n*[[Vitusapotek]]\n*[[Western Norway Pharmaceutical Trust]]\n\n==Philippines==\n<!-- PLEASE DON'T ADD PHARMACIES THAT DO NOT HAVE ARTICLES. -->\n\n*[[Mercury Drug]]\n*[[Rose Pharmacy]]\n*[[South Star Drug]]\n*[[Watsons]]\n\n==Poland==\n<!-- PLEASE DON'T ADD PHARMACIES THAT DO NOT HAVE ARTICLES. -->\n\n*[[Super-Pharm]]\n\n==Puerto Rico==\n<!-- PLEASE DON'T ADD PHARMACIES THAT DO NOT HAVE ARTICLES. -->\n\n*[[CVS Health|CVS]]\n*[[Walgreens]]\n\n===Defunct chains===\n<!-- PLEASE DON'T ADD PHARMACIES THAT DO NOT HAVE ARTICLES. -->\n\n*[[Farmacias El Amal]]\n\n==Singapore==\n<!-- PLEASE DON'T ADD PHARMACIES THAT DO NOT HAVE ARTICLES. -->\n\n*[[Guardian Pharmacy]]\n*[[Watsons]] Pharmacy\n\n==Sweden==\n<!-- PLEASE DON'T ADD PHARMACIES THAT DO NOT HAVE ARTICLES. -->\n\n*[[Apoteket]]\n*[[Celesio|Doc Morris]]\n\n==Taiwan==\n<!-- PLEASE DON'T ADD PHARMACIES THAT DO NOT HAVE ARTICLES. -->\n\n*[[Watsons]]\n\n==Thailand==\n<!-- PLEASE DON'T ADD PHARMACIES THAT DO NOT HAVE ARTICLES. -->\n\n*[[Alliance Boots]]\n*[[General Nutrition Centers|GNC]]\n*[[Watsons]]\n\n==United Kingdom==\n<!-- PLEASE DON'T ADD PHARMACIES THAT DO NOT HAVE ARTICLES. -->\n\n*[[Asda]] Pharmacy\n*[[Boots Pharmacy]]\n*[[Gordons Chemist]] \n*[[Lloyds Pharmacy]]\n*[[Morrisons]] Pharmacy\n*[[Superdrug]] Pharmacy\n*[[Tesco]] Pharmacy\n*[[Well Pharmacy]]\n\n===Other pharmacies===\n<!-- PLEASE DON'T ADD PHARMACIES THAT DO NOT HAVE ARTICLES. -->\n\n*[[Numark (pharmacy)|Numark]]{{spaced ndash}}buying group of over 2,000 independently owned pharmacies in the UK\n\n===Internet pharmacies===\n<!-- PLEASE DON'T ADD PHARMACIES THAT DO NOT HAVE ARTICLES. -->\n\n*[[Pharmacy2U]] \u2013 online mail-order pharmacy located in the UK\n*[[Medexpress]] \u2013 online mail-order pharmacy located in the UK\n\n==United States==\n<!-- PLEASE DON'T ADD PHARMACIES THAT DO NOT HAVE ARTICLES. -->\n\nMany pharmacy chains in the United States are owned and operated by regional [[supermarket]] brands, or national [[big-box store]] brands such as [[Walmart]]. These pharmacies are located within their larger chain stores. The three largest free-standing pharmacy chains in the United States are [[Walgreens]], [[CVS Pharmacy|CVS]], and [[Rite Aid]].\n\nAlthough not a pharmacy chain, many of the fairly ubiquitous Costco stores include a pharmacy and - in California at least - the pharmacy is available to non-members.\n\n*[[Giant-Carlisle|Ahold Financial Services (Giant)]]\n*[[BI-LO (United States)|BI-LO Inc.]]\n*[[Cerberus Capital Management|Cerberus Capital (Albertsons)]]\n*[[Costco|Costco Pharmacies]]\n*[[CVS Health|CVS Corporation]]\n*[[Fred's|Fred's Inc.]]\n*[[Giant Eagle|Giant Eagle Pharmacy]]\n*[[Giant-Landover|Giant Food Inc.]]\n*[[H-E-B|H E B Drug Stores]]\n*[[Hy-Vee|Hy-Vee Inc.]]\n*[[Kaiser Permanente|Kaiser Permanente (HMO)]]\n*[[Kroger|Kroger Company]]\n*[[Cardinal Health|Medicine Shoppe International]]\n*[[Meijer|Meijer Groceries]]\n*[[Omnicare]]\n*[[Publix|Publix Pharmacies]]\n*[[Rite Aid|Rite Aid Corporation]]\n*[[Safeway Inc.|Safeway]]\n*[[Sears Holdings|Sears Holdings Corporation (Kmart)]]\n*[[Shopko|Shopko Stores Inc.]]\n*[[ShopRite (United States)|Shoprite Supermarkets Inc.]]\n*[[SuperValu (United States)|Supervalu Inc.]]\n* [[Target Corporation|Target]] \u2013 pharmacies are operated by CVS\n*[[Walgreens]]\n*[[Walmart|Walmart Stores Inc.]]\n\n===Stand-alone pharmacy chains===\n{{div col end}}{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n<!-- PLEASE DON'T ADD PHARMACIES THAT DO NOT HAVE ARTICLES. -->\n\n*[[Bartell Drugs]]\n*[[Boone Drug]]\n*[[CVS Pharmacy]]\n*[[Discount Drug Mart]]\n*[[Drug Emporium]]\n*[[Duane Reade]] (subsidiary of [[Walgreens]] since 2010; operates as separate brand name)\n*[[Family Pharmacy]]\n*[[Good Neighbor Pharmacy]]\n*[[Hartig Drug]]\n*[[Health Mart]]\n*[[Kinney Drugs]]\n*[[Leader Drug Stores]]\n*[[Lewis Drug]]\n*[[Longs Drugs]] (subsidiary of CVS since 2008)\n*[[Medicine Shoppe Pharmacy]]\n*[[Navarro Discount Pharmacies]] (subsidiary of CVS since 2015)\n*[[Rite Aid]]\n*[[Thrifty White]]\n*[[Valu-Rite]]\n*[[Walgreens]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n===Defunct chains===\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n<!-- PLEASE DON'T ADD PHARMACIES THAT DO NOT HAVE ARTICLES. -->\n\n*[[Arbor Drugs]] (acquired by [[CVS Corporation|CVS]] in 1998)\n*[[Big B Drugs]] (acquired by Revco in 1996; rebranded as CVS in 1997)\n*[[Brooks Pharmacy]] (acquired by [[Rite Aid]] in 2007)\n*[[Cunningham Drug (U.S.)|Cunningham Drug]] (acquired by Walgreens in 1991)\n*[[Dart Drug]] (bankrupt in 1990)\n*[[Drug Fair]] (company liquidated in 2009, assets purchased by [[Walgreens]])\n*Dwayne international pharmacy (CVS in 1996)\n*[[Eckerd Corporation|Eckerd]] (acquired by [[Rite Aid]] in 2007)\n*[[Fay's Drug]] (purchased by JC Penney and rebranded as Eckerd in 1997)\n*[[Farmacias El Amal]]\n*[[G.O. Guy]] (purchased by Pay'n'Save in 1987)\n*[[Genovese Drug Stores]] (acquired by Eckerd parent [[J. C. Penney]] in 1998; rebranded in 2003)\n*[[Gray Drug]] (Bought by Rite Aid in 1987)\n*[[Happy Harry's]] (bought by Walgreens in 2006; rebranded in 2011)\n*[[Hook's Drug Stores]] (acquired by [[Revco]] in 1994)\n*[[IDL Drug Stores]]\n*[[Jean Coutu Group|Jean Coutu]] (US stores acquired by Rite Aid in 2004)\n*[[K&B]] (Acquired by Rite Aid in 1997)\n*[[Kerr Drug]] (acquired by Walgreens in 2013)\n*[[Lane Drug]] (purchased by Rite Aid in 1989)\n*[[LaVerdiere's]] (purchased by Rite Aid in 1994)\n*[[Stop & Shop|Medi Mart]] (sold to [[Walgreens]] in 1980s)\n*[[Osco Drug]] (freestanding stores acquired by and converted to [[CVS Corporation|CVS]] in 2006)\n*[[Pay 'n Save]] (acquired by Thirfty Corp. in 1988, rebranded as PayLess Drug)\n*[[Thrifty PayLess|PayLess Drug Stores]] (purchased by Rite Aid in 1996)\n*[[Peoples Drug]] (acquired by CVS in 1990; rebranded in 1994)\n*[[Perry Drug Stores]] (acquired by Rite Aid in 1995)\n*[[Phar-Mor]] (bankrupt in 2002)\n*[[Revco]] (bought by CVS in