-------------------------\n-->\n\n{{Refimprove|date=April 2017}}\n\nThis article is a list of major '''[[pharmacy|pharmacies]]''' (also known as '''chemists''' and '''drugstores''') by country.\n{{TOC right}}\n\n==Australia==\n<!-- PLEASE DON'T ADD PHARMACIES THAT DO NOT HAVE ARTICLES. -->\n\nPharmacies in Australia are mostly independently owned by [[pharmacists]], often operated as [[franchising|franchises]] of retail brands offered by the three major pharmaceutical wholesalers in Australia: [[Australian Pharmaceutical Industries]] (API) and [[Sigma Pharmaceuticals]]. A minority of pharmacies are owned by [[Friendly society|friendly societies]], particularly in [[Victoria (Australia)|Victoria]] and [[South Australia]].\n\n* [[Chemist Warehouse]]\n\n===API brands===\n<!-- PLEASE DON'T ADD PHARMACIES THAT DO NOT HAVE ARTICLES. -->\n\n*[[Priceline (Australia)|Priceline Pharmacies]]\n*[[Soul Pattinson]]{{spaced ndash}}formerly owned by [[Washington H. Soul Pattinson|Washington H. Soul Pattinson & Co. Ltd]]\n\n===Symbion brands===\n<!-- PLEASE DON'T ADD PHARMACIES THAT DO NOT HAVE ARTICLES. -->\n\n*[[Terry White Chemmart]]\n\n==Canada==\n[[image:Pharmaprix.2.1.jpg|thumb|right|250px|Pharmaprix drugstore in Alma]]\n<!-- PLEASE DON'T ADD PHARMACIES THAT DO NOT HAVE ARTICLES. -->\n\n*[[Brunet (pharmacy)|Brunet]]\n*[[Costco]]\n*[[Loblaw Companies|DRUGStore Pharmacy]]\n*[[Familiprix]]\n*[[Jean Coutu Group|Jean Coutu]]\n*[[Katz Group of Companies]]\n*[[Lawtons]]\n*[[London Drugs]]\n*[[PharmaChoice]]\n*[[Pharmasave]]\n*[[Proxim (pharmacy)|Proxim]] (merger of [[Essaim]] and [[Sant\u00e9 Services]])\n*[[Rexall]]\n*[[Shoppers Drug Mart]] (Pharmaprix in Quebec)\n*[[Uniprix]]\n*[[Value Drug Mart]]\n*[[Walmart]]\n\n===Defunct chains===\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n<!-- PLEASE DON'T ADD PHARMACIES THAT DO NOT HAVE ARTICLES. -->\n\n*[[Cadieux]] (acquired by [[Jean Coutu Group|Jean Coutu]] in 1987)\n*[[Cumberland Drugs]] (acquired by [[Uniprix]] 53 and [[Jean Coutu Group|Jean Coutu]] 19 in 1997)\n*[[Superpharm]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n==China==\n<!-- PLEASE DON'T ADD PHARMACIES THAT DO NOT HAVE ARTICLES. -->\n\nThe key players in the drugstore industry in China are:\n*[[China Nepstar]] \u2013 Shenzhen-based; China's largest\n*[[Super-Pharm]] \u2013 Israeli company; had about 65 stores in China as of 2007\n*[[Watsons]]  \u2013 owned by HK-based Hutchison Whampoa\n\n==Denmark==\n<!-- PLEASE DON'T ADD PHARMACIES THAT DO NOT HAVE ARTICLES. -->\n\nIn Denmark, all pharmacies are owned by the [[Association of Danish Pharmacies]] and controlled by the state. There are two pharmaceutically trained groups with a [[higher education]] in the Danish pharmacies: [[pharmaconomist]]s ({{lang-da|farmakonomer}}) and [[pharmacist]]s ({{lang|da|farmaceuter}}). There are also [[pharmacy technician]]s ({{lang|da|defektricer}}) who have a [[vocational training]] and [[Laborer|unskilled laborers]]/[[Blue-collar worker|workers]] ({{lang|da|servicemedarbejdere}}) who perform [[manual labour]].\n\n==Germany==\n<!-- PLEASE DON'T ADD PHARMACIES THAT DO NOT HAVE ARTICLES. -->\n\nIn Germany, pharmacies are known as \"apotheken\". Like France, they are all independently owned by pharmacists, and like France, there are no pharmacy chains.\n\n===Online pharmacy===\n*[[Celesio]]\n\n==Hong Kong==\n<!-- PLEASE DON'T ADD PHARMACIES THAT DO NOT HAVE ARTICLES. -->\n\n*[[Mannings]]\n*[[Watsons]]\n\n==India==\n<!-- PLEASE DON'T ADD PHARMACIES THAT DO NOT HAVE ARTICLES. -->\n*[[MedPlus]] Health Services\n*Apollo\n*[[Medlife]]\n*Medcare\n*Thulsi\n*POP\n\nOnline\n\n* [[Medlife]]\n* [[Medplus|Medplus Mart]]\n* 1mg\n* Netmeds\n* Pharmeasy\n* 1Tab\n\n==Ireland==\n<!-- PLEASE DON'T ADD PHARMACIES THAT DO NOT HAVE ARTICLES. -->\n\n*[[Lloyds Pharmacy]]\n\n==Israel==\n<!-- PLEASE DON'T ADD PHARMACIES THAT DO NOT HAVE ARTICLES. -->\n[[File:Arad Mall outside.jpg|thumb|A [[Super-Pharm]] in [[Arad, Israel|Arad]], [[Israel]]]]\n\n*[[Super-Pharm]]\n\n==Macau==\n<!-- PLEASE DON'T ADD PHARMACIES THAT DO NOT H